Third-party documentation bundled for the markstay dogfood study
================================================================

The files under this directory are sampled, unmodified pages from two open-source
documentation projects, each then stamped with markstay `stay:` markers (the only
change made to the source text). They are redistributed here under their original
licenses solely as a reproducible evaluation corpus. See corpus/manifest.json for
the exact upstream commit and file list, and prepare_public_corpus.py to regenerate
from upstream.

fastapi/  --  FastAPI documentation
  Source : https://github.com/fastapi/fastapi  (docs/en/docs)
  Commit : 0cb4a8e284b450abbccb71c543ad7757de46c0b2
  License: MIT
  Copyright (c) 2018 Sebastián Ramírez

rust-book/  --  The Rust Programming Language ("the Rust Book")
  Source : https://github.com/rust-lang/book  (src)
  Commit : 05d114287b7d6f6c9253d5242540f00fbd6172ab
  License: MIT OR Apache-2.0
  Copyright (c) 2010 The Rust Project Developers

The full MIT and Apache-2.0 license texts are available in the upstream
repositories linked above. markstay itself is unaffiliated with FastAPI or the Rust
project; these corpora are used only as representative real-world Markdown.
